      <item>
        <title>Unix Command Line Tips &amp; Tricks</title>
        <description>Below are some handy command line tips and tricks.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;You can read the rest with &quot;Ubuntu Unleashed 2015 Edition&quot;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;!! - Run last command&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;For Example:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span
        style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;Hierro -&amp;gt; echo &quot;Saluton Mondo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;Saluton Mondo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;Hierro -&amp;gt; !!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span
        style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;echo &quot;Saluton Mondo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;Saluton Mondo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span
        style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span
        style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;You can even combine it with other commands.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;For example:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span
        style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;sudo !! will run sudo echo &quot;Saluton Mondo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;!*(bang star)&lt;/b&gt; - This is a tricky one. This one will print out the last thing terminal spit out.
&lt;br/&gt;The below command will allow you nano the file from the ls command.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span
        style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;Hierro -&amp;gt; ls testFile2.txt&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;testFile2.txt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;Hierro -&amp;gt; nano !*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;nano testFile2.txt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Used alone, it will print out the last thing in the terminal and use it as a command like below&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;span
            style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;Hierro -&amp;gt; echo &quot;echo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;span
            style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;Hierro -&amp;gt; !* &quot;hello&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;&quot;echo&quot; &quot;hello&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;courier new&amp;quot; , &amp;quot;courier&amp;quot; , monospace;&quot;&gt;hello&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span
